LATE SEPTEMBER tracked three wide, inched closer to the top pair while under strong urging in the four path turning for home, took aim on the new leader in upper stretch, wrestled place in midstretch, and chased the clear leader home well through the final furlong. CALIBRACHOA KID tugged forward to set the pace outside of a rival around the first turn, inched forward to a clear margin entering the backstretch, showed the way in the two path into the far turn as that foe re-applied outside pressure, got headed by that one at the five sixteenths pole, yielded while losing place in midstretch, and displayed blood from his mouth suggesting having bit his tongue. I DON'T VENMO settled off of the pace the pace in the two path, raced between horses around the far turn, altered course outwardly in upper stretch, and stayed on willingly. KAJUN KARMA raced forwardly two wide and between horses, chased the leading trio turning for home, and lacked a bid. MANGUM was void of speed in the early stages, trailed along the inside around both turns, and moved up between horses in upper stretch. MOR BIG LEE was keen racing behind foes approaching the first turn, floated to the five path entering that bend while well off of the pace, then took the far turn in the four path, and made little impact. BENOIT tracked from midpack along the inside, but weakened with three furlongs to go.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: KING'S GLORY set the pace inside of an outer pressing foe around the turn, shook free of that one entering the lane, maintained a clear margin through midstretch, and was put to wraps while holding sway entering the final sixteenth. CASTLEWARDEN gained to track the leading pair from a few lengths off while outside of a rival into the turn, but bumped and shied from that foe approaching the five sixteenths pole, sustained a grinding rally after shifting three wide in upper stretch, gained place at the furlong grounds with multiple lengths to find on the clear leader, but flopped back to his left lead and lugged inwardly approaching the sixteenth pole, and failed to threaten late. BILLY JACK tracked along the inside, was joined in pursuit by an outer CASTLEWARDEN nearing the turn, but shied while bumping with that rival approaching the five sixteenths pole causing a hard steady, recovered nearing the lane, altered course four wide in upper stretch, and rallied to gain show at the sixteenth pole. HARBOUR BRIDGE broke a step slow, took the turn in the three path while off of the pace, and stayed on mildly. COACHES MEETING broke inwardly at the start, then saved ground off of the pace, but to no avail. NOBLE REALITY (FR) pressed the eventual winner from the outside around the turn, but failed to keep pace entering the lane, and faltered in the final furlong. BILLY BOB ROCKET lacked speed two wide and between horses early on, and never got involved. RIVER RAFT broke outwardly while off slow, trailed in the four path around the turn, fanned wider entering the lane before his rider lost his crop in upper stretch, and showed little. RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR MOMENT left the gates well, took the lead, attended the pace from the rail , was never challenged, drew off. ALPINE MIST was slow getting into stride, raced along the rail smartly saving ground this trip, sat four off of the leader for the first three and half furlongs, started advancing after the half, was encouraged starting in the upper stretch and responded with a persistent drive that wore down the rest of the rivals and she was able to claim second place honors. LOUISIANA LIBERTY was slow getting started, was three wide racing through the first turn, was allowed to find her stride and was unhurried until the half mile pole, was slightly encouraged to pick up her pace ,after the half, responded well and was cued at the three eighths pole, gamely circled the field and was in position at the quarter pole, was encouraged and raced through the stretch , was able to finish third. FREE DROP MADDY stalked the pace three wide, was within striking distance and poised while racing down the backside, was asked at the three eights pole and responded with a run, but the leader was able to keep the same distance between herself and FREE DROP MADDY, struggled down the lane and as the distance increased she eventually stopped. GUITAR WOMAN was sent out of the gates, took the first turn three wide and win between horses, raced three and four wide through out, was in between horses for the first half of a mile, was asked at the half mile pole and ended up matching strides with the same for who was on her outside the whole race, was pressure through the turn and tired after the quarter pole. OLIVIA G was five wide through the first turn, chased the early leaders past the six furlong pole, finally settled along the outside of the set of horses that were just off the leader, asked after the half and matched strides with an inner for, they battled through the second turn and OLIVIA G tired by the quarter pole.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG CHOPPER tracked along the inside under a snug hold, saved ground around the turn, produced a rail bid passing the furlong pole, forged an advantage inside the final sixteenth, and desperately lasted to the wire from a quickly on-charging rival. BRIAN'S IRON MIKE broke slowly, raced off of the pace in the three path, came under a firm hold between horses into the turn before fanning to the five path to be outside of the main group approaching the five sixteenths pole, spun in to the lane in the six path, delayed a lead change until the furlong grounds, but surged outside of rivals after changing over, offered a late bid in hopes of reeling in the leader at the wire, but narrowly came up short. BERTIE'S GALAXY took a bump from an outer rival at the start, prompted the pace outside of the leader, pressed in the three path around the turn got floated to the four path entering the lane, wrestled an advantage approaching the furlong grounds, but shifted inwardly and into his inner counterpart's path at the furlong grounds, got headed by a rail bidder in the final sixteenth, and yielded between horses late. BRON AND BROW rated off of the pace in the two path, and chased willingly through the lane while not menacing. RELENTLESS DANCER stalked behind the top pair and from the three path, shifted to the five path to take aim outside of them entering the lane, but lacked a bid. YANKEE SEVEN set the pace inside of a pressing rival while remaining a bit off of the rail around the turn, resisted that foe's bid while spinning into the lane in the three path, but got headed approaching the final furlong, steadied when his outer counterpart shifted into him soon after, and faltered between horses in the late stages. FIESTY FIST bumped an inner rival at the start, chased the top pair from the four path, and gave way entering the lane. X CLOWN bobbled before being bumped by rivals on both sides and checking out of crowded quarters at the start, trailed along the inside, then greenly refused to change leads through the lane, and got outrun. VODKA GIMLET was urged along to chase from midpack while hung in the six path into the turn, and tired.
